article.headline: Louisiana Tech 77, Centenary 71
article.story: BOSSIER CITY, La. -- Jamel Guyton scored 22 to lead Louisiana Tech to a 77-71 win over Centenary on Saturday night. Kyle Gibson added 20 points for the Bulldogs (5-4), who won their third straight game. David Jackson chipped in with 15 points and nine rebounds. Kenneth Cooper finished with 12 points and 11 rebounds for Louisiana Tech. The Gents (2-9) were led by Nick Stallings, who scored 25 points on 8 of 17 shooting. Gary Redus added 18 points. Louisiana Tech outrebounded Centenary 43-24. They also shot 46.9 percent from the field (23-for-49), including 50 percent from 3-point range (7-for-14). Centenary has now lost four straight games.
